Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of knowledge-based programs (KBPs) in AI planning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the succinctness and complexity of plans, which are topics related to programming languages and compilers (cs.PL) and logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper mentions on-line computation time, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and the complexity of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS).
